@* Forum.Web/Components/Layout/MudProviders.razor *@
@* MudBlazor's providers must be interactive for popovers (MudSelect!), dialogs
   and snackbars to work, but MainLayout must stay static (@Body cannot cross a
   render-mode boundary). So the providers live in their own interactive island
   — the same pattern as NavAuthControls. Every InteractiveServer island on a
   page shares one circuit and its scoped services, so interactive pages find
   the popover provider. Prerender stays ON so the theme's <style> is part of
   the initial HTML (no unthemed flash). *@
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using Forum.Web.Common

<MudThemeProvider Theme="QuorumTheme.Theme" IsDarkMode="true" />
<MudPopoverProvider />
<MudDialogProvider />
<MudSnackbarProvider />
